      <section eId="sec_9_12_2">
        <num>9-12-2</num>
        <content>
          <p>In the trial of all civil cases, the judge upon request of the jury shall furnish the jury with written instructions as to the form of their verdict.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 3480; Code 1868, § 3502; Code 1873, § 3560; Ga. L. 1880-81, p. 115, § 1; Code 1882, § 3560; Civil Code 1895, § 5330; Civil Code 1910, § 5925; Code 1933, § 110-103.)</p>
